<taxonomicName authorityName="Blas &amp; Navarro" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Blas &amp; Navarro" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[293,566,1717,1742]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bergiantina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilzingeri">
<emphasis box="[293,566,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="33">Bergiantina hilzingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from other 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1222,1717,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bergiantina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[979,1124,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="33">Bergiantina</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: a) forewing ground color opaque reddish orange, densely covered with white scales; b) basal and antemedial lines diffuse; and c) left plate of vesica of aedoeagus with a single lateral tooth strongly sharpened with narrow base.
</paragraph>
